Source: schoolbell
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Brian Sutherland <jinty@web.de>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.1.16), python, python2.3-dev (>= 2.3.2)
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: schoolbell
Section: misc
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python:Depends},ssl-cert, openssl, zope3.1-python2.3-schoolbell (= ${Source-Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: web server for co-ordinating schedules, timetables and calendars
 SchoolBell is a free and open source application to allow groups and
 organizations to coordinate schedules and timetables.  Users may manage their
 personal calendars, group calendars and calendars for resources, e.g., rooms,
 projectors, etc, via a web interface, or using an iCalendar compliant client
 such as Mozilla calendar or iCal. SchoolBell is written in Python, and is a
 Zope 3 component.
 .
 This package contains the configuration and the binaries to run a standalone
 SchoolBell server.
 .
 Homepage: http://www.schooltool.org/schoolbell

Package: libschoolbell
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: common architecture dependent files for the SchoolBell server
 SchoolTool is a project to develop a common global school administration
 infrastructure that is freely available under an Open Source licence.
 .
 This package contains all of the architecture dependent parts of SchoolBell
 server. All of these are derived from Zope 3, whose components are included in
 the package. This package will dissapear when a Zope 3.1 package arrives
 containing these components.
 .
 Homepage: http://www.schooltool.org/schoolbell

Package: zope3.1-python2.3-schoolbell
Section: misc
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python:Depends}, python2.3-pyopenssl, python2.3-xml, python2.3-twisted (>= 1.3.0), libxml2-python2.3 (>= 2.6.3-1), python2.3-imaging, libschoolbell (= ${Source-Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: python2.3-tcpwrap (>= 0.2)
Description: web server for co-ordinating schedules, timetables and calendars
 SchoolBell is a free and open source application to allow groups and
 organizations to coordinate schedules and timetables.  Users may manage their
 personal calendars, group calendars and calendars for resources, e.g., rooms,
 projectors, etc, via a web interface, or using an iCalendar compliant client
 such as Mozilla calendar or iCal. SchoolBell is written in Python, and is a
 Zope 3 component.
 .
 This package contains the SchoolBell python module. (And, temporarily, quite a
 bit of Zope 3)
 .
 Homepage: http://www.schooltool.org/schoolbell
